  {%- if ph == 'blog-about-tokiyo-lifestyle' -%}
  <article class="article-hub__article">
    <header class="article-hub__header">
      <span class="text-eyebrow">Brand &amp; Stories</span>
      <h1>About Tokiyo Lifestyle</h1>
      <p class="article-hub__meta">By Tokiyo Lifestyle Team · July 2026</p>
    </header>
    <div class="article-hub__image"><img src="{{ 'hero-slide-1.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Tokiyo Lifestyle Brand Story" loading="eager"></div>
    <div class="article-hub__body">
      <p><strong>Tokiyo Lifestyle</strong> was born at the crossroads of Japanese minimalism and Indian street culture — a brand built not just to sell clothing, but to tell a story with every thread. Founded with the belief that premium quality should be accessible to every ambitious young Indian, Tokiyo brings together oversized silhouettes, bold graphic storytelling, and heavyweight 240 GSM cotton into one identity.</p>
      <h2>Our Philosophy</h2>
      <p>We believe clothes are more than fabric. They are declarations. When you wear a Tokiyo piece, you are choosing a garment that was designed with intention — from the weight of the cotton to the precision of the print, every detail is deliberate.</p>
      <h2>The Name: Tokiyo</h2>
      <p>Tokiyo (トキーヨ) draws inspiration from the word <em>tokiyo</em> in Japanese philosophy — a concept of living fully in the present moment while building towards the future. This dual energy — grounded yet ambitious — is what we embed into every collection.</p>
      <h2>Made for India, Inspired by the World</h2>
      <p>From the neon-lit streets of Tokyo to the chai stalls of Mumbai, our aesthetic blends global and local. We create streetwear that feels at home whether you are at a college campus in Delhi or an airport lounge in Bangalore. Our garments are built for movement, for life, for expression.</p>
      <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Premium 240 GSM super-combed cotton for every piece</li>
        <li>Drop-shoulder engineered construction for perfect drape</li>
        <li>DTF and puff printing for graphics that last</li>
        <li>Custom luxury packaging — because the unboxing is part of the experience</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We are more than a clothing brand. We are a lifestyle. Welcome to Tokiyo.</p>
    </div>
  </article>

  {%- elsif ph == 'blog-story-behind-every-design' -%}
  <article class="article-hub__article">
    <header class="article-hub__header">
      <span class="text-eyebrow">Brand &amp; Stories</span>
      <h1>The Story Behind Every Design</h1>
      <p class="article-hub__meta">By Tokiyo Creative Studio · July 2026</p>
    </header>
    <div class="article-hub__image"><img src="{{ 'hero-slide-2.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Story Behind Tokiyo Designs" loading="eager"></div>
    <div class="article-hub__body">
      <p>Every graphic on a Tokiyo tee starts as a hand-drawn sketch. Our in-house design studio in India works with a blend of Japanese calligraphy influences, anime-inspired line art, and bold typographic expressions to create graphics that feel both timeless and culturally resonant.</p>
      <h2>From Concept to Cloth</h2>
      <p>The process begins with a mood board — sourced from everything from Shinjuku street photography to vintage Bollywood poster art. Our designers then translate these references into original vector illustrations, refined over multiple rounds of feedback before they ever touch a t-shirt.</p>
      <h2>Why We Choose DTF Printing</h2>
      <p>Direct-to-film (DTF) printing allows us to achieve photographic detail and unlimited colour depth — something traditional screen printing cannot match for complex artwork. Our prints are heat-cured at precise temperatures to ensure they survive hundreds of wash cycles without cracking or fading.</p>
      <h2>Limited Drops, Intentional Stories</h2>
      <p>We do not mass produce. Each Tokiyo collection is a limited drop — typically 200–500 units per design. This scarcity is intentional. We want every customer to own something rare, something with meaning. When a drop sells out, it stays sold out.</p>
      <p>The next time you look at a graphic on your Tokiyo tee, know that it took weeks of creative work — and a team of passionate people — to get it there.</p>
    </div>
  </article>

