    <div class="article-hub__image"><img src="{{ 'hero-slide-4.png' | asset_url }}" alt="T-Shirt Colors for Skin Tone" loading="eager"></div>
    <div class="article-hub__body">
      <p>Colour theory is simple once you understand undertones. Here is a practical guide to which Tokiyo colours work best for different Indian skin tones.</p>
      <h2>Fair Skin (Cool Undertones)</h2>
      <p>Black, deep navy, and bold reds create beautiful contrast against fair skin. Avoid very pale pastels that can wash you out. Pista green and airforce blue work beautifully. White is universally flattering at every skin tone.</p>
      <h2>Medium / Wheatish Skin (Neutral to Warm Undertones)</h2>
      <p>The broadest range works here. Beige, camel, mustard, and warm earth tones enhance natural warmth. Black creates striking contrast. Whites look especially clean. Avoid very pale yellow-adjacent pastels that can look muddy.</p>
      <h2>Darker Skin (Warm Undertones)</h2>
      <p>Vibrant colours pop beautifully — bold reds, bright whites, deep blacks all look incredible. Beige and mustard complement warm undertones. Lavender and soft pastels provide beautiful contrast. Avoid muted, chalky versions of any colour.</p>
      <h2>The Universal Rule: Confidence</h2>
      <p>Skin tone is a starting point for colour guidance, not a restriction. The most important factor in any outfit is confidence. Wear what you love. The right colour is always the one you feel best in.</p>
    </div>
  </article>

